                George L's Cable Products




                Make a cable in seconds, clean up that tangled pedalboard, or redo your rack in minutes. It's easy and fast if you use George L's Solderless Plugs and Cable. Your cable makes the difference in how your performance is rated for sound.

                
                Enjoy the sound of your instrument without the noise and buzz that outside interference can cause. George L's special anti-stat in the cable reduces the microphonics and allows your music to flow without the problems of hum, buzz, or microphonics while you play. Have you ever stepped on your cable while playing and broken the connection to your plug? This problem is easily remedied with George L's solderless connection cables.  Just reapply your plug, tighten down the set screw and you're done in seconds!

                
                You will always sound your best with George L's Solderless Plugs and Cable. So if you want to rewire your studio or play like the pros, we have the cable and plugs to fit your needs. Remember, your instrument is only as good as the cables that carry your music to the ears of your fans. High quality is what made George L's famous and now you too can master the art of superb audio recognition.

                
"It's my favorite cable ever made for guitar! " -Eric Johnson

Voted #1 for sound clarity by Guitar Player Magazine, Sept. 1997






            George L's Cable - By the Foot: 
            We carry both the lighter .155 cable for pedalboard/studio wiring, as well as the heavier .225 cable for making longer stage-friendly cables. The .155 cable is now available in orange, blue, black, red, and purple; the .225 is available in black or red. You will always sound your best with George L's Solderless Plugs and Cable. So if you want to rewire your studio or play like the pros, we have the cable and plugs to fit your needs. Remember, your instrument is only as good as the cables that carry your music to the ears of your fans.
            
NOTE: .155 plugs will only fit on .155 cable, and .225 plugs will only fit on .225 cable.
 



