Instructions for Assembling George L's Cable & Plugs

Straight Plugs Assembly:

DO NOT STRIP CABLE.
                  Cut with a sharp instrument. Make it straight and clean.
                  Back set screw out, far enough to allow cable to pass.
                  Put plug on cable and push plug on to the needle. This is your hot connection.
                  Tighten set screw down to touch the cable. Then tighten the screw 1 1/2 - 2 rotations. This is the ground connection.
                

Right Angle Plugs Assembly:

DO NOT STRIP CABLE.
                  Cut with a sharp instrument. Make it straight and clean.
                  Remove cap from right angle plug
                  Push cable onto the needle. DO NOT FORCE, and HOLD CABLE WITH YOUR THUMB.
                  Bend cable enough to start screwing the cap back on. Let the twisting of the cap bring the cable down.
                  Screw cap down completely to create the ground.
                






























